  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  QRS&gt; 150 ms or 120-150ms associated dyssynchrony

          -  The etiology can be idiopathic, ischemic, hypertensive and Chagas' disease

          -  Ejection fraction &lt;35%

          -  The optimal pharmacological treatment for heart failureExclusion Criteria:

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with pulmonary diseases, neurological diseases, renal, skeletal muscle
             diseases

          -  Patients with contraindications to implant a cardiac pacemaker

          -  Pregnancy

          -  New York Heart Association functional class IV

          -  Atrial fibrillation
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>18 Years</minimum_age>
    <maximum_age>70 Years</maximum_age>
